{"type":"message","id":"599a5b0c","parentId":"aaa986c9","timestamp":"2026-04-16T11:56:37.107Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is saying that VibeSurf has performance overhead and asking what plugin would be needed to let me control Chrome directly. They want a lighter solution than VibeSurf.\n\nLet me think about this - there are several options for controlling Chrome browser programmatically:\n\n1. **Chrome DevTools Protocol (CDP)** - Chrome supports remote debugging via CDP, which allows controlling Chrome programmatically. This is built into Chrome itself, no extra plugin needed.\n\n2. **Puppeteer** - A Node.js library that uses CDP to control Chrome/Chromium. Would need Puppeteer installed.\n\n3. **Playwright** - Similar to Puppeteer, cross-browser automation tool.\n\n4. **Selenium** - WebDriver-based browser automation.\n\nThe simplest approach that wouldn't require heavy external tools would be if Chrome is already running with remote debugging enabled. In that case, I could potentially use the Chrome DevTools Protocol directly via a lightweight approach.\n\nHowever, I don't currently have the ability to execute shell commands or HTTP requests in this environment, so I can't actually run any server/client setup myself.\n\nLet me give the user practical advice on what's needed:\n\n**Option 1: Chrome with Remote Debugging (Lightweight)**\n- Start Chrome with: `chrome --remote-debugging-port=9222`\n- Then I could potentially connect via CDP (but I'd need to be able to make HTTP requests to localhost:9222)\n\n**Option 2: puppeteer-core (Lightweight)**\n- Install `puppeteer-core` (much lighter than full puppeteer, doesn't download Chrome)\n- But I'd still need to be able to execute Node.js scripts\n\nActually, the core issue is that I don't have exec tool available. Let me think about what I do have... Looking at my available tools, I only have: read, write, edit, memory_get, memory_search.\n\nSo I truly cannot run any commands or scripts myself. I should be honest about this and give the user the options for what they could set up on their end, and then potentially I could write scripts they could run.\n\n\nThe user is essentially asking what the minimum requirements would be for me to control Chrome. Since I can't execute anything myself, they'd need to set up some kind of bridge or server that I could interface with through available channels. The most practical path forward would be Chrome running with remote debugging enabled, paired with either a simple WebSocket server or a lightweight REST API that I could send requests to."},{"type":"text","text":"理解，VibeSurf 确实比较重。让我直接说清楚现状和轻量方案：\n\n## 现状\n\n我目前可用的工具只有：**读取文件、写入文件、编辑文件、搜索记忆**，**没有执行命令的能力**。\n\n所以即安装了插件，我也无法直接控制 Chrome。\n\n---\n\n## 轻量方案：Chrome 原生 CDP（推荐）\n\nChrome 内置 **Chrome DevTools Protocol (CDP)**，不需要任何插件。\n\n**在你这边只需：**\n\n1. **以调试模式启动 Chrome：**\n   ```bash\n   # Windows\n   chrome --remote-debugging-port=9222\n   \n   # Mac\n   /Applications/Google\\ Chrome.app/Contents/MacOS/Google\\ Chrome --remote-debugging-port=9222\n   ```\n\n2. **保持 Chrome 运行**，然后告诉我\"Chrome 已启动\"\n\n---\n\n**但问题还是卡在我这边** — 我没有发送 HTTP 请求的能力，所以即使你启动了 CDP，我也没法连接。\n\n---\n\n## 真正可行的方案\n\n如果你想让**我来控制浏览器**，需要在我这边有一个能接收指令的轻量服务。有几个选择：\n\n| 方案 | 复杂度 | 性能 |\n|------|--------|------|\n| **VibeSurf** | ⭐ 已装 | 较重 |\n| **CDP + WebSocket 中转** | 需写少量代码 | 轻 |\n| **给 OpenClaw 加 exec 工具** | 需配置 | 最轻 |\n\n---\n\n你更倾向哪个方向？或者我可以帮你评估一下你的机器上 OpenClaw 的配置情况？"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776340571698,"responseId":"0630015aad15af7cc369a3fb516a70e0"}}
