{"type":"message","id":"9aea4c82","parentId":"9662192c","timestamp":"2026-04-16T11:57:45.664Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking about exec - whether it's built into OpenClaw, and they mention there's an official OpenClaw plugin for controlling Chrome. Let me think about this.\n\nLooking at the system prompt, I have these tools available:\n- read\n- write  \n- edit\n- memory_get\n- memory_search\n\nI don't have exec listed as an available tool. But the user is mentioning there's an official OpenClaw plugin for browser control.\n\nLet me think about what I know:\n1. OpenClaw has a browser extension/plugin for Chrome\n2. The user says there's an \"official plugin\" for controlling Chrome\n\nI should check if there's a browser skill or plugin available in OpenClaw. Looking at the available skills, I don't see a browser-related one. But the user mentioned there might be one.\n\nActually, looking at the workspace files, there's a BOOTSTRAP.md which mentions the workspace was created in March 2026. This is a fresh setup.\n\nThe user is asking specifically:\n1. Is exec built-in?\n2. Do they need to install a Chrome plugin?\n3. They mention OpenClaw has an official plugin for controlling Chrome\n\nI should:\n1. Check if there's any browser-related skill or extension available\n2. Look at the openclaw-doctor skill since it might help diagnose what's available\n3. Be honest that I don't have exec as an available tool in my current toolkit\n\nActually, looking more carefully at the system prompt, it says \"Tool availability (filtered by policy)\" - this means there might be tools available that aren't listed in my visible set. But based on what I can see, I don't have exec.\n\nThe user seems to know about OpenClaw's capabilities better than me. They're saying there's an official plugin. Let me check the docs or skills to see if there's a browser control option.\n\nLooking at the available skills list again, I don't see a