{"type":"message","id":"3bfcc62d","parentId":"a84246d5","timestamp":"2026-04-16T12:04:10.845Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Looking at the config, I can see:\n\n1. `plugins.allow` includes `browser` - so that's not the issue\n2. `plugins.entries.browser.enabled` is `true` - also good\n3. The `tts` agent has `browser` in its `tools.allow` list\n\nBut the user said `capabilities=none`. Let me look more carefully at the tts agent config:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"id\": \"tts\",\n  \"name\": \"选品专家\",\n  \"workspace\": \"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace/Selector\",\n  \"agentDir\": \"/home/halei/.openclaw/agents/tts/agent\",\n  \"model\": \"gemini/gemini-2.0-flash\",\n  \"tools\": {\n    \"allow\": [\n      \"cron\",\n      \"read\",\n      \"write\",\n      \"edit\",\n      \"apply_patch\",\n      \"memory_search\",\n      \"memory_get\",\n      \"browser\",\n      \"message\"\n    ]\n  }\n}\n```\n\nSo `browser` IS in the tts agent's tools.allow list. That's not the issue.\n\nWait - the runtime info says:\n```\nRuntime: agent=tts | host=halei-Surface-Pro-4 | repo=/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace/Selector | os=Linux 6.8.0-106-generic (x64) | node=v24.14.0 | model=minimax/MiniMax-M2.7 | default_model=gemini/gemini-2.0-flash | shell=bash | channel=feishu | capabilities=none | thinking=off\n```\n\nBut the tts agent config says `model: \"gemini/gemini-2.0-flash\"` and `agents.defaults.model.primary: \"minimax/MiniMax-M2.7\"`. \n\nThe runtime shows `model=minimax/MiniMax-M2.7` even though the tts agent should be using gemini/gemini-2.0-flash. This suggests the tts agent might not actually be in use right now - the user is probably chatting with the main agent instead, which doesn't have browser in its tools.allow list (only main does, and even there it's incomplete).\n\nWait, but the inbound metadata shows `chat_id: user:ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68` and the bindings indicate tts should route to feishu/tts while main routes to feishu/kiit. The routing seems correct, yet the runtime model doesn't match what tts is configured for. I need to check what model the main agent is actually using to understand why minimax is showing up instead of gemini.\n\nLooking at the capabilities=none issue, the browser tool is listed in the allow rules for both agents, but it's not actually available. This could mean the browser plugin isn't fully initialized, the browser service isn't running, or there's something else preventing it from loading properly despite being permitted.\n\nLet me restart the gateway first since that often resolves plugin loading issues. If that doesn't work, I'll check the browser profile status directly on the user's machine."},{"type":"text","text":"配置看起来没问题——`browser` 已经在 `plugins.allow` 和 tts agent 的 `tools.allow` 中了。\n\n问题可能是 **Gateway 需要重启** 才能加载 browser 插件。\n\n请运行：\n\n```bash\nopenclaw gateway restart\n```\n\n然后再告诉我\" Gateway 已重启\"，我测试一下浏览器控制是否可用。"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776341027245,"responseId":"063003244cfa81d44dc30510b740ea93"}}
