{"type":"message","id":"f4a3b430","parentId":"76518b9a","timestamp":"2026-04-16T12:07:42.193Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user restarted the gateway. Now let me try to use the browser tool to take a screenshot or check the status. Since I have `capabilities=none` normally, I wonder if the browser tool will work this time.\n\nActually, looking at the system prompt more carefully:\n- `capabilities=none` in the Runtime section\n- But `browser` is in the `tools.allow` list for the tts agent\n\nWait, I think the issue might be that I need to use the `browser` tool directly. Looking at the docs, the agent gets one consolidated `browser` tool that handles all browser operations. Let me try to call it.\n\nBut I don't have a `browser` tool available in my function list - I only have `read`, `write`, `edit`, `memory_get`, `memory_search`. So the browser capability must be injected separately by OpenClaw based on the session.\n\n\nI'm realizing the `capabilities=none` in the runtime info might be misleading - the actual tool availability depends on what OpenClaw injects when the session starts, not what's visible in my initial function list. Since browser is configured in the tts agent's tools.allow, it should be available to me even though I'm not seeing it in my initial function set.\n\nLet me just try calling the browser tool directly and see if it works - if it's not available, the worst that happens is I get an error back."},{"type":"text","text":"好，让我测试一下 browser 工具：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_n35ozsj2rvl4_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/halei/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/browser.md","offset":800,"limit":30}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776341249174,"resp