{"type":"message","id":"8bed8d4a","parentId":"f4a3b430","timestamp":"2026-04-16T12:07:42.338Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_n35ozsj2rvl4_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n```bash\nopenclaw browser wait \"#main\" \\\n  --url \"**/dash\" \\\n  --load networkidle \\\n  --fn \"window.ready===true\" \\\n  --timeout-ms 15000\n```\n\n## Debug workflows\n\nWhen an action fails (e.g. “not visible”, “strict mode violation”, “covered”):\n\n1. `openclaw browser snapshot --interactive`\n2. Use `click <ref>` / `type <ref>` (prefer role refs in interactive mode)\n3. If it still fails: `openclaw browser highlight <ref>` to see what Playwright is targeting\n4. If the page behaves oddly:\n   - `openclaw browser errors --clear`\n   - `openclaw browser requests --filter api --clear`\n5. For deep debugging: record a trace:\n   - `openclaw browser trace start`\n   - reproduce the issue\n   - `openclaw browser trace stop` (prints `TRACE:<path>`)\n\n## JSON output\n\n`--json` is for scripting and structured tooling.\n\nExamples:\n\n\n[140 more lines in file. Use offset=830 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776341262319}}
{"type":"message","id":"ba3097a3","parentId":"8bed8d4a","timestamp":"2026-04-16T12:07:59.634Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The system/runtime says `capabilities=none`. But looking at the config, `browser` IS in the `plugins.allow` list and in the `tts` agent's `tools.allow` list. The browser plugin entry is also enabled.\n\nThe issue might be that the browser tools (`browser.*`) are exposed through the browser plugin, and even though the plugin is enabled, the tool itself might not be registered properly for this agent.\n\nWait - looking more carefully at the config:\n```json\n\"tts\": {\n    \"id\": \"tts\",\n    \"name\": \"选品专家\",\n    \"workspace\": \"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace/Selector\",\n    \"agentDir\": \"/home/halei/.openclaw/agents/tts/agent\",\n    \"model\": \"gemini/gemini-2.0-flash\",\n    \"tools\": {\n      \"allow\": [\n        \"cron\",\n        \"read\",\n        \"write\",\n        \"edit\",\n        \"apply_patch\",\n        \"memory_search\",\n        \"memory_get\",\n        \"browser\",  // <--- browser IS in the allow list\n        \"message\"\n      ]\n    }\n  }\n```\n\nThe `tools.allow` list has `browser` but not specifically `browser.*`. According to the browser docs, the agent gets one tool called `browser` with sub-actions (status/start/stop/tabs/open/focus/close/snapshot/screenshot/navigate/act).\n\nSo the tool name is just `browser`, and it's in the allow list. It should work...\n\nUnless there's something about how the browser plugin exposes the tool. Let me think about this differently.\n\nThe `capabilities=none` at runtime is concerning. This might be a display issue in my runtime context injection, or it might genuinely mean the browser tool isn't available.\n \nMaybe the browser plugin just needs a bit more time to initialize after the restart. I should give it another moment and try again. Though honestly, I'm not entirely sure what's preventing the browser tool from working—it's definitely in the config and should be allowed. The agent might just not have picked it up yet from the runtime injection."},{"type":"text","text":"让我再等一下再试——Gateway 重启后 browser 插件需要几秒初始化。\n\n[[reply_to_current]] \n\n等等...我发现问题了。你配置的是 **`user` profile**（attach 到你已登录的 Chrome），但这个 profile 需要单独配置。让我确认一下当前 browser 状态：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_evq847ycobsb_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/halei/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/browser.md","offset":830,"limit":50}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776341262341,"responseId":"0630040e1cf2526301da298b1a752447"}}
{"type":"message","id":"3e3f7759","parentId":"ba3097a3","timestamp":"2026-04-16T12:07:59.722Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_evq847ycobsb_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"```bash\nopenclaw browser status --json\nopenclaw browser snapshot --interactive --json\nopenclaw browser requests --filter api --json\nopenclaw browser cookies --json\n```\n\nRole snapshots in JSON include `refs` plus a small `stats` block (lines/chars/refs/interactive) so tools can reason about payload size and density.\n\n## State and environment knobs\n\nThese are useful for “make the site behave like X” workflows:\n\n- Cookies: `cookies`, `cookies set`, `cookies clear`\n- Storage: `storage local|session get|set|clear`\n- Offline: `set offline on|off`\n- Headers: `set headers --headers-json '{\"X-Debug\":\"1\"}'` (legacy `set headers --json '{\"X-Debug\":\"1\"}'` remains supported)\n- HTTP basic auth: `set credentials user pass` (or `--clear`)\n- Geolocation: `set geo <lat> <lon> --origin \"https://example.com\"` (or `--clear`)\n- Media: `set media dark|light|no-preference|none`\n- Timezone / locale: `set timezone ...`, `set locale ...`\n- Device / viewport:\n  - `set device \"iPhone 14\"` (Playwright device presets)\n  - `set viewport 1280 720`\n\n## Security & privacy\n\n- The openclaw browser profile may contain logged-in sessions; treat it as sensitive.\n- `browser act kind=evaluate` / `openclaw browser evaluate` and `wait --fn`\n  execute arbitrary JavaScript in the page context. Prompt injection can steer\n  this. Disable it with `browser.evaluateEnabled=false` if you do not need it.\n- For logins and anti-bot notes (X/Twitter, etc.), see [Browser login + X/Twitter posting](/tools/browser-login).\n- Keep the Gateway/node host private (loopback or tailnet-only).\n- Remote CDP endpoints are powerful; tunnel and protect them.\n\nStrict-mode example (block private/internal destinations by default):\n\n```json5\n{\n  browser: {\n    ssrfPolicy: {\n      dangerouslyAllowPrivateNetwork: false,\n      hostnameAllowlist: [\"*.example.com\", \"example.com\"],\n      allowedHostnames: [\"localhost\"], // optional exact allow\n    },\n  },\n}\n```\n\n## Troubleshooting\n\n[90 more lines in file. Use offset=880 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776341279716}}
{"type":"message","id":"df26ed72","parentId":"3e3f7759","timestamp":"2026-04-16T12:08:16.219Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me try to directly call the browser tool. I need to look at the browser tool definition more carefully to understand how to invoke it.\n\nActually, looking at my available tools, I only have:\n- read\n- write  \n- edit\n- memory_search\n- memory_get\n\nI don't have a `browser` tool available directly. The docs mention that the `browser` tool is supposed to be injected by the browser plugin, but it's not showing up in my tool list.\n\nWait - looking at the config again, the `tts` agent has `browser` in its tools.allow list. But maybe the browser plugin is not properly loaded.\n\nActually, let me think about this differently. The user is saying they restarted the gateway. Maybe I should just try to interact with the browser via a tool call and see what happens.\n\nBut I don't have any tool that lets me call exec or send HTTP requests. All I have is read/write/edit/memory_search/memory_get.\n\nLet me look at the problem from a different angle. The issue is:\n1. The browser plugin needs to be loaded\n2. The browser tool needs to be injected into the agent\n3. I don't have exec/HttpRequest tools to test the browser API directly\n\nMaybe I should ask the user to verify that the browser plugin is loaded by running a command and sharing the output. Or maybe I should try to directly use the browser tool that should be available.\n\nActually, wait. Let me re-read the browser documentation. It says:\n> The agent gets **one tool** for browser automation:\n> - `browser` — status/start/stop/tabs/open/focus/close/snapshot/screenshot/navigate/act\n\nThis `browser` tool should be auto-injected by the browser plugin. If it's not in my available tools, it means either:\n1. The browser plugin failed to load\n2. The browser tool isn't being routed to me\n\nLet me ask the user to run `openclaw browser status` to check the browser status, since this is a CLI command they can run and share the output of. This will help diagnose if the browser plugin is loaded and what profiles are available."},{"type":"text","text":"抱歉，我这边仍然没有 browser 工具可用。这说明 browser 插件可能还没有成功加载。\n\n**帮我运行一下这个命令，把结果发给我：**\n\n```bash\nopenclaw browser status\n```\n\n以及：\n\n```bash\nopenclaw plugins list\n```\n\n这样我能确认 browser 插件的状态，看看到底卡在哪里。"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776341279723,"responseId":"063004206a8e355938e7534f3893cba7"}}
