{"type":"message","id":"ac3cb199","parentId":"d5d3e215","timestamp":"2026-04-16T12:08:47.379Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user says they can see their computer screen and want to know if I can control the browser. They haven't sent the output of the commands I asked for. Let me try to proceed based on what I know.\n\nActually, I notice my capabilities still show `capabilities=none` in the runtime info at the top of this conversation. So browser tools are still not available to me.\n\nWait - but maybe the user is telling me they can see their screen and want me to try? Maybe they've done something to enable it?\n\nLet me re-read the runtime info: `capabilities=none | thinking=off`. So browser is still not available.\n\nBut the user is asking \"可以控制吗\" (can you control it?) and saying they can see their computer screen. Maybe they want me to try anyway?\n\nI should be honest - my capabilities still show no browser tools. But let me check if maybe there's something I can do. The user seems eager to try.\n\nActually wait - I should check if the Gateway restart changed anything. Let me look at the current session status. But I don't have a way to check my own capabilities dynamically.\n\nLet me be honest with the user: my capabilities still show `none` for browser. But since they mention they can see their screen, maybe they've done something. Let me ask them to confirm what they see, or ask them to send me a screenshot of what they see on their screen so I can help them.\n\nActually, the more likely situation is: the user is asking \"can you control it?\" referring to whether the browser is working. They might have run the commands and are waiting to see if I can now do something.\n\nLet me try a different approach - maybe I should try calling the browser tool anyway even if it seems unavailable. But I don't have any tool that would let me call browser... wait, I have `read`, `write`, `edit`, `memory_search`, `memory_get` only.\n\n\nLooking at my available tools, there's nothing that would let me execute browser commands - no exec, no process, no subagents listed. So I literally cannot call the browser even if it were working. I need to be direct with the user: my available tools are `read`, `write`, `edit`, `memory_search`, and `memory_get`, which means I can't execute any browser commands regardless of whether the browser tool is enabled in the system."},{"type":"text","text":"抱歉，我现在只有 `read`、`write`、`edit`、`memory_search`、`memory_get` 这几个工具，**没有可以执行命令或调用 browser 的能力**。\n\n所以即使用户那边 browser 插件已加载，我也无法发送指令给它。\n\n---\n\n**目前有两个可行方案：**\n\n### 方案一：让我有 exec 能力（最直接）\n需要给 OpenClaw 开启 exec 工具，这样我就能执行 `openclaw browser` 命令来控制 Chrome。\n\n### 方案二：你在终端操作，我来指挥\n你在终端里执行命令，把结果截图发给我，我告诉你下一步操作什么。\n\n---\n\n你更倾向哪个？或者如果你愿意给我开 exec 权限，我可以告诉你怎么配置。"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776341302641,"responseId":"0630043710c5e439d384e7afaee1f79b"}}
