{"type":"message","id":"0cdaf924","parentId":"1b56e9b5","timestamp":"2026-04-16T12:20:18.020Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"System (untrusted): [2026-04-16 20:18:30 GMT+8] Exec failed (cool-pin, signal SIGKILL)\nSystem (untrusted): [2026-04-16 20:18:46 GMT+8] Exec completed (brisk-va, code 0) :: /home/halei/.n/bin/npx npm warn exec The following package was not found and will be installed: chrome-devtools-mcp@0.21.0 0.21.0\nSystem: [2026-04-16 20:20:14 GMT+8] Feishu[tts] DM | ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68 [msg:om_x100b5139798090a0c4f3d4e6fa6acd7]\n\nConversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b5139798090a0c4f3d4e6fa6acd7\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68\",\n  \"sender\": \"ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Thu 2026-04-16 20:17 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68\",\n  \"name\": \"ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68\"\n}\n```\n\n我给你这个实例安装插件后， 下次你在开启还能保存吗"}],"timestamp":1776342018015}}
{"type":"message","id":"b9d23aa9","parentId":"0cdaf924","timestamp":"2026-04-16T12:20:34.761Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking: if they install a plugin/extension in the Chrome browser instance that I'm controlling, will it persist the next time I start the browser?\n\nThere are two Chrome instances here:\n1. The `openclaw` profile - a separate, isolated Chrome instance that OpenClaw manages. This uses its own user data directory, so any extensions installed there would persist within that profile.\n\n2. The `user` profile - which attaches to the user's existing Chrome session at `chrome://inspect/#remote-debugging`. This reuses the user's actual Chrome profile, so extensions installed in the user's regular Chrome would already be available.\n\nThe user seems to be talking about the `openclaw` profile (the isolated instance). If they install an extension in that profile, it should persist because the `openclaw` profile maintains its own user data directory.\n\nHowever, I should clarify which Chrome instance they're referring to. Let me explain:\n\n- For the `openclaw` managed browser: Extensions installed will persist because it has its own user data directory\n- For the `user` profile (your existing Chrome): Extensions you install in your Chrome normally will be available\n\nLet me give a clear answer about this."},{"type":"text","text":"好问题！取决于你用的是哪个实例：\n\n---\n\n## 1. `openclaw` 独立实例（我刚才启动的）\n\n- 有**独立的数据目录**\n- 在这个实例里安装的插件/扩展 **会保存**\n- 下次启动时仍然可用\n- ⚠️ 但这个实例**没有你的登录状态**（echotik 需要重新登录）\n\n---\n\n## 2. `user` 实例（你当前的 Chrome）\n\n- 复用的是你**真实 Chrome** 的配置\n- 你在这个 Chrome 里正常安装的插件，**一直都在**\n- 你的登录状态、cookies **全部保留**\n- ✅ **推荐方案** — 一次配置，以后永久生效\n\n---\n\n## 建议\n\n既然你已经在 `user` 实例里打开了 echotik，**直接在 `user` 实例操作就好**：\n\n- 在你的 Chrome 里登录 echotik（如果你还没登录）\n- 我通过 `user` profile 来控制你的 Chrome\n- 你安装的插件会保留，你登录的状态也会保留\n\n---\n\n你想用哪个方案？\n1. **继续用 `user` 实例**（推荐，你已经配置好了）\n2. **用 `openclaw` 独立实例**（扩展会保存，但需要重新登录）"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776342018020,"responseId":"06300702c886693ee8e084d06bed37ad"}}
