{"type":"message","id":"af9b3d44","parentId":"3010ede8","timestamp":"2026-04-16T12:21:01.788Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking about the difference between the two browser instances. They seem to be confirming that using the \"user\" instance shows the browser being controlled, while the standalone \"openclaw\" instance doesn't. Let me clarify this.\n\nThe key difference:\n1. `user` profile - connects to YOUR real Chrome that YOU can see on screen, so when I control it, you see the movements\n2. `openclaw` profile - opens a separate Chrome instance that runs in the background, so you can't see it on screen\n\nThe user is confirming this understanding is correct."},{"type":"text","text":"对，就是这样：\n\n---\n\n**`user` 实例（你的 Chrome）**\n- 你**能看见**浏览器里的操作\n- 页面加载、点击、滚动——你都能看到\n- ✅ 适合需要你**监督/确认**的操作\n\n---\n\n**`openclaw` 独立实例**\n- 运行在**后台**，你**看不见**\n- 适合纯后台任务（数据采集等）\n- 但截图看不到实际画面\n\n---\n\n所以用 `user` 实例是正确的选择！你现在应该能看到我在你的 Chrome 上打开了 echotik.live。\n\n**你可以随时看着我操作，不需要担心\"偷偷搞什么\"** 😄\n\n---\n\nGateway 重启好了告诉我，我们继续下一步！"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776342052679,"responseId":"063007255020f50a980e76ca28d2441a"}}
