{"type":"message","id":"e533084e","parentId":"8ec0f247","timestamp":"2026-04-16T12:22:13.213Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[media attached: /home/halei/.openclaw/media/inbound/ea590883-43cb-401f-8d4b-b52cb27486e8.jpg (image/jpeg) | /home/halei/.openclaw/media/inbound/ea590883-43cb-401f-8d4b-b52cb27486e8.jpg]\nTo send an image back, prefer the message tool (media/path/filePath). If you must inline, use MEDIA:https://example.com/image.jpg (spaces ok, quote if needed) or a safe relative path like MEDIA:./image.jpg. Avoid absolute paths (MEDIA:/...) and ~ paths - they are blocked for security. Keep caption in the text body.\nSystem: [2026-04-16 20:21:58 GMT+8] Feishu[tts] DM | ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68 [msg:om_x100b51390880d4a8c3446d1a90d750a, post, 1 attachment(s)]\n\nConversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b51390880d4a8c3446d1a90d750a\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68\",\n  \"sender\": \"ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Thu 2026-04-16 20:21 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68\",\n  \"name\": \"ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68\"\n}\n```\n\n[Image]\nUser text:\n[Feishu ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68 Thu 2026-04-16 20:21 GMT+8] ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68: /home/halei/.openclaw/media/inbound/ea590883-43cb-401f-8d4b-b52cb27486e8.jpg\n但是这个被控制功能 刚刚的实例没有，控制我的就有\nDescription:\nThe image shows a Google Chrome browser window displaying a page from **erp.91miaoshou.com**. Below the address bar, a notification bar warns in Chinese: \"Chrome is being controlled by automated test software,\" next to an orange button that says \"Turn off in 'Settings'.\" At the bottom, a teal header features a white geometric logo and the Chinese text for \"**Miaoshou ERP Help Center**.\" The screenshot captures a browser automation warning while visiting a help article."}],"timestamp":1776342133205}}
{"type":"message","id":"e078a574","parentId":"e533084e","timestamp":"2026-04-16T12:22:23.448Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is showing me a screenshot of their Chrome browser with the message \"Chrome is being controlled by automated test software\" (Chrome 正在接收自动测试软件的控制). This confirms that the `user` profile (their Chrome) is indeed being controlled by OpenClaw - they can see the automation notice in their Chrome window.\n\nThe user is saying that the \"being controlled\" indicator appears in their Chrome (controlled), but not in the standalone `openclaw` instance (not controlled).\n\nThis is exactly right! The standalone `openclaw` instance runs in a separate process/window, so there's no \"being controlled\" indicator visible in the regular Chrome. But when using the `user` profile that attaches to their actual Chrome, Chrome shows this automation notice.\n\nSo everything is working correctly. The user is just confirming that they see the automation notice in their Chrome, which is the expected behavior when being controlled via the `user` profile.\n\nI should confirm this is correct and ask them what they want to do next."},{"type":"text","text":"对！这就是**被控制的样子** 😄\n\n\"Chrome 正在接收自动测试软件的控制\" — 这个提示只会出现在**你的 Chrome** 被控制时，独立的 `openclaw` 实例不会有（因为它是独立的浏览器进程）。\n\n---\n\n**✅ 一切正常！**\n\n你现在看到的就是我通过 `user` profile 控制你 Chrome 的状态。\n\n---\n\n接下来你想做什么？比如：\n\n1. **登录 echotik 账号**\n2. **导航到选品页面（泰国/越南站点）**\n3. **其他操作**\n\n告诉我指令就行！"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776342133213,"responseId":"063007758fe9858f5d0f6843bec0b0d3"}}
