{"type":"message","id":"08db87dc","parentId":"fcb95a54","timestamp":"2026-04-16T12:24:24.514Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"System: [2026-04-16 20:24:22 GMT+8] Feishu[tts] DM | ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68 [msg:om_x100b513901adb8a4c357be5fcd220dc]\n\nConversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b513901adb8a4c357be5fcd220dc\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68\",\n  \"sender\": \"ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Thu 2026-04-16 20:24 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68\",\n  \"name\": \"ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68\"\n}\n```\n\n我要求证一个问题， 就是 显示和不显示浏览器被控制的， 对应的网站都能检测出来吗"}],"timestamp":1776342264509}}
{"type":"message","id":"9ee9933f","parentId":"08db87dc","timestamp":"2026-04-16T12:24:47.280Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking whether websites can detect that they're being controlled by automation software, regardless of whether the \"controlled by automated test software\" message is shown or not.\n\nThis is a good technical question. Let me think about this:\n\n1. **\"Controlled by automated test software\" message** - This is a Chrome-level notification that appears when Chrome is launched with remote debugging enabled or when CDP (Chrome DevTools Protocol) is attached. This is a browser-level indicator visible to the user.\n\n2. **Website detection** - Websites can detect automation through various methods:\n   - **WebDriver detection** - `navigator.webdriver` flag is set to `true` when controlled by automation\n   - **Chrome DevTools Protocol presence** - Some sites check for CDP-related properties\n   - **Automation-specific attributes** - Like `window.document.__webdriver_evaluate`, `window.domAutomationController`, etc.\n   - **Headless browser signatures** - Some sites detect headless mode\n   - **Behavior-based detection** - Unusual mouse movements, timing patterns, etc.\n\nSo the answer is:\n- The \"controlled by automated test software\" message is just a **user-level notification** (visible in Chrome's UI)\n- But websites can still detect automation through various JavaScript APIs regardless of whether this message is shown or not\n- The `openclaw` standalone instance might actually be easier to detect because it uses Playwright/CDP directly\n- The `user` profile (existing Chrome with remote debugging) might be harder to detect because it uses the official Chrome DevTools MCP, which is more \"legitimate\"\n\nLet me give a clear, accurate answer."},{"type":"text","text":"好问题！让我解释清楚：\n\n---\n\n## 两个概念\n\n| | 用户可见提示 | 网站检测能力 |\n|---|---|---|\n| **你的 Chrome（user profile）** | ✅ 有提示 | ❌ 仍然可检测 |\n| **openclaw 独立实例** | ❌ 无提示 | ❌ 同样可检测 |\n\n---\n\n## 网站检测自动化 ≠ 看那个提示\n\n那个 \"Chrome 正在被自动测试软件控制\" 提示只是**给你的浏览器加的标签**，网站本身有**独立的检测方式**：\n\n### 网站能检测到的常见信号：\n- `navigator.webdriver === true`（自动化特征 flag）\n- 缺失的浏览器插件/功能\n- 不正常的浏览器指纹\n- 鼠标轨迹、点击节奏像机器人\n\n### 实际上：\n- **user profile**（你的 Chrome）用的是官方 Chrome DevTools MCP，**更难被检测**\n- **openclaw 独立实例**用 Playwright 启动，**更容易被检测**\n\n---\n\n## 结论\n\n- 那个提示只是**安慰用户**的，网站不在乎这个\n- **你的 Chrome 被控制**（user profile）反而比独立实例**更难被网站检测到**\n\n所以用 `user` profile 是对的 ✅"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776342264514,"responseId":"063007f9ae10b0f9ae1fa9efa4fde19c"}}
